This paper discusses the use of virtual reality as a training tool for robotic setup, which involves both human-computer interaction (HCI) and robotics (RO). The paper also touches on the graphical representation of the virtual environment, which falls under computer graphics (GR). Additionally, the paper discusses the reproducibility and consistency of the training, which could be related to cybersecurity (CYBER) and machine learning (LG) techniques. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.HC, followed by cs.RO, cs.GR, cs.CYBER, and cs.LG.
